commit.message: Fixed name of the python-dateutil dependency

Changed cron weekdays to match the cron standard

Previously, APScheduler used 0-6 to mean Monday-Sunday. This differs from the cron standard where 0 meant Sunday. This change breaks backwards compatibility which means it could not have been fixed in v3.x.

Fixes #286.

Refactored the triggers

Triggers are now stateful, allowing for correct operation of the combining triggers. They are also JSON serializable now.
Removed the tagging step and fixed PR handling
Fixed the name of the test extras in tox.ini

Fixed changelog screwups due to the v4.0 rebase operation

Fixes #382.
Updated skipif markers to work with newer versions of pytest

Fixed OverflowError on QT scheduler if the wait time is very long

Fixes #371.

Fixed wrong method name in documentation (#374)

The function name is `add_job`.
Fixed methods inherited from base class could not be executed by processpool executor (#367)

Replaced @yield_fixture with @fixture

@yield_fixture has been deprecated for a while.
Adapted RethinkDBJobStore to rethinkdb library v2.4+

Removed skipping of Gevent tests on Python 3.7

Recent versions of Gevent now work properly with Python 3.7.

Added a FAQ entry about serialization related ValueErrors

Credit goes to Jeff Vandrew Jr. for doing the initial work in PR #357.
